                <example>
                    <title>Median (2)</title>
                    <p>To find the median age of the Best Actress Oscar winners, we first need to
                        order the data. It would be useful, then, to use the stemplot, a diagram in
                        which the data are already ordered.</p>
                    <p> Here n = 44 (an even number), so the median M, will be the mean of the two
                        center observations. These are located at the n / 2 = 44 / 2 = <em>22nd</em>
                        and n / 2 + 1 = 44 / 2 + 1 = <em>23rd</em> spots. Counting from the top, we
                        find that:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>the 22nd ranked observation is 34</li>
                        <li>the 23rd ranked observation is 35</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>Therefore, the median <m:math overflow="scroll">
                            <m:mrow>
                                <m:mi>M</m:mi>
                                <m:mtext> </m:mtext>
                                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                                <m:mtext> </m:mtext>
                                <m:mfrac>
                                    <m:mrow>
                                        <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                                        <m:mn>34</m:mn>
                                        <m:mtext> </m:mtext>
                                        <m:mo>+</m:mo>
                                        <m:mtext> </m:mtext>
                                        <m:mn>35</m:mn>
                                        <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                                    </m:mrow>
                                    <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                                </m:mfrac>
                                <m:mtext> </m:mtext>
                                <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                                <m:mtext> </m:mtext>
                                <m:mn>34.5</m:mn>
                            </m:mrow>
                        </m:math>
                    </p>
